This%20is%20not%20consumers%20running%20out%20and%20taking%20vacations%20and%20buying%20second%20homes%20and%20a%20new%20car%20or%20anything%20like%20that%2C%20quite%20the%20contrary%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economist%20underscored%20that%20households%20are%20drawing%20down%20their%20savings%20and%20running%20up%20their%20credit%20cards%20just%20to%20cover%20everyday%20expenses%2C%20and%20cutting%20back%20on%20non-essential%20purchases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInflation%20spiked%20to%20a%2040-year%20high%20of%20more%20than%209%25%20in%202022%2C%20and%20has%20been%20tracking%20close%20to%204%25%20in%20recent%20months%20%E2%80%94%20well%20above%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%202%25%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20central%20bank%20has%20responded%20by%20hiking%20interest%20rates%20from%20nearly%20zero%20to%20north%20of%205%25%2C%20which%20has%20raised%20the%20monthly%20amount%20that%20people%20owe%20on%20their%20mortgages%2C%20credit%20cards%2C%20car%20loans%2C%20and%20other%20debts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20one-two%20punch%20of%20surging%20prices%20and%20soaring%20borrowing%20costs%20has%20put%20the%20squeeze%20on%20households%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20raid%20their%20piggy%20banks%2C%20rack%20up%20additional%20debt%2C%20save%20less%20each%20month%2C%20and%20slash%20their%20outgoings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPomboy%20pointed%20to%20the%20National%20Restaurant%20Association's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frestaurant.org%2Fresearch-and-media%2Fresearch%2Feconomists-notebook%2Frestaurant-performance-index%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emonthly%20performance%20index%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bshockingly%20weak%26quot%3B%20reading%20in%20January%20as%20consumers%20dined%20out%20less%2C%20and%20remained%20depressed%20in%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20emphasized%20that%20retail%20sales%20have%20barely%20budged%20in%20two%20years%20once%20adjusted%20for%20inflation.%20Moreover%2C%20she%20highlighted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%