rd%20Scolyer%2C%20a%20leading%20Australian%20doctor%2C%20is%20marking%20a%20year%20of%20being%20%26quot%3Bcancer-free%26quot%3B%20after%20a%20groundbreaking%2C%20self-administered%20treatment.%20Diagnosed%20with%20aggressive%20brain%20cancer%20(glioblastoma)%20last%20year%20while%20in%20Poland%2C%20Professor%20Scolyer%2C%20then%2057%2C%20defied%20the%20odds.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20type%20of%20cancer%20typically%20has%20a%20survival%20rate%20of%20just%2012%20months.%20Drawing%20on%20his%20expertise%20in%20melanoma%20research%2C%20Professor%20Scolyer%20opted%20for%20an%20experimental%20treatment%20he'd%20developed.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemarkably%2C%20a%20recent%20MRI%20scan%20revealed%20no%20sign%20of%20the%20tumour.%20%C2%A0Professor%20Scolyer%20collaborated%20with%20his%20friend%20and%20colleague%2C%20Professor%20Georgina%20Long%2C%20%C2%A0both%20co-directors%20of%20the%20Melanoma%20Institute%20Australia.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20achievements%20were%20recognized%20with%20the%20prestigious%20Australian%20of%20the%20Year%20award.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-australia-69006713%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBBC%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ereports%20indicate%20this%20approach%20enhances%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20immunotherapy.%20Professor%20Scolyer%20became%20the%20first%20brain%20cancer%20patient%20to%20receive%20this%20pre-surgical%20treatment%20regimen%20last%20year.%20While%20he%20endured%20a%20difficult%20post-treatment%20period%20with%20seizures%2C%20liver%20issues%2C%20and%20pneumonia%2C%20he's%20now%20experiencing%20improved%20health%20and%20is%20%26quot%3Bcancer-free%26quot%3B%20a%20year%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20be%20honest%2C%20I%20was%20more%20nervous%20than%20I%20have%20been%20for%20any%20previous%20scan.%20I'm%20just%20thrilled%20and%20delighted%2C%20couldn't%20be%20happier.%20I'm%20the%20best%20I%20have%20felt%20for%20yonks.%20It%20certainly%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20my%20brain%20cancer%20is%20cured%2C%20but%20it's%20just%20nice%20to%20know%20that%20it%20hasn't%20come%20back%20yet%2C%20so%20I've%20still%20got%20some%20more%20time%20to%20enjoy%20my%20life%20with%20my%20wife%20Katie%20and%20my%20three%20wonderful%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20Professor%20Richard%20Scolyer%20told%20the%20portal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Georgina%20Long%20shared%2C%20%26quot%3BWe've%20generated%20a%20whole%20heap%20of%20data%2C%20to%20then%20make%20a%20foundation%20for%20that%20next%20step%2C%20so%20that%20we%20can%20help%20more%20people.%20We're%20not%20there%20yet.%20What%20we%20have%20to%20really%20focus%20on%20is%20showing%20that%20this%20pre-surgery%2C%20combination%20immunotherapy%20type%20of%20approach%20works%20in%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20of%20Professor%20Richard%20Scolyer%20has%20ignited%20excitement%20in%20the%20fight%20against%20brain%20cancer.%20%C2%A0Professor%20Scolyer%2C%20a%20leader%20in%20melanoma%20research%2C%20opted%20for%20a%20novel%20immunotherapy%20treatment%20co-developed%20with%20Professor%20Georgina%20Long.%20%C2%A0Early%20results%2C%20as%20reported%20in%20a%20recently%20submitted%20scientific%20paper%2C%20are%20promising.%20%C2%A0This%20approach%2C%20targeting%20approximately%20300%2C000%20brain%20cancer%20diagnoses%20annually%2C%20could%20revolutionize%20treatment.%20%C2%A0While%20the%20primary%20goal%20is%20to%20extend%20Professor%20Scolyer's%20life%2C%20the%20long-term%20aim%20is%20to%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20wider%20clinical%20trials.%20Professor%20Long%20cautions%20that%20a%20fully%20approved%20treatment%20will%20still%20require%20significant%20development%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715768640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fmpggl4eo_professor-richard-scolyer_625x300_15_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Faustralian-doctor-beats-brain-cancer-with-self-invented-treatment-im-thrilled-5668732%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Their%20achievements%20were%20recognized%20with%20the%20prestigious%20Australian%20of%20the%20Year%20award.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Faustralian-doctor-beats-brain-cancer-with-self-invented-treatment-im-thrilled-5668732%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Faustralian-doctor-beats-brain-cancer-with-self-invented-treatment-im-thrilled-5668732%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Faustralian-doctor-beats-brain-cancer-with-self-invented-treatment-im-thrilled-5668732%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20moved%20to%20NYC%20from%20Ukraine%20for%20a%20tech%20job.%20Here%20are%203%20main%20differences%20in%20America's%20work%20culture.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221980%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yaroslav%20Zubko%20wearing%20a%20white%20T-shirt%20and%20sitting%20in%20a%20lecture%20hall.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6643284bb4abc992e8c932dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221485%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYaroslav%20Zubko%20moved%20to%20the%20US%20to%20work%20for%20a%20startup%20in%20New%20York.%3Cp%3ENatalia%20Azarkina%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EYaroslav%20Zubko%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20in%202017%20after%20building%20up%20his%20tech%20career%20in%20Ukraine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe's%20noticed%20key%20differences%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Ukraine%20tech%20work%20culture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EZubko%20said%20people%20in%20the%20US%20overwork%20more%20and%20place%20more%20emphasis%20on%20idea%20generation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%2034-year-old%20Yaroslav%20Zubko%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20New%20York%2C%20about%20his%20experience%20moving%20to%20the%20US%20for%20a%20tech%20job.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20I%20traveled%20to%20New%20York%20for%20a%20two-week%20business%20trip.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20time%20I'd%20ever%20left%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffled-ukraine-when-war-started-moved-colorado-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkraine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20I%20grew%20up.%20I%20looked%20at%20all%20the%20huge%20buildings%20in%20the%20city%20and%20couldn't%20believe%20my%20eyes.%20New%20York%20was%20even%20more%20impressive%20than%20it%20seemed%20in%20the%20movies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20made%20a%20promise%20to%20myself%20that%20I%20was%20going%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-nyc-from-london-mistakes-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emove%20to%20New%20York%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20I%20was%20offered%20a%20role%20as%20a%20director%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmade-244000-freelance-product-designer-ateam-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproduct%20design%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20New%20York%20tech%20startup%20called%20UpTop.%20I%20hadn't%20been%20actively%20applying%20for%20US%20jobs%20at%20the%20time.%20They%20supported%20me%20in%20getting%20a%20visa%2C%20and%20I%20moved%20to%20NYC%20in%20June%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20to%20America%20has%20been%20the%20biggest%20adventure%20of%20my%20life.%20But%20the%20tech%20culture%20is%20very%20different%20in%20the%20US%20than%20in%20Ukraine.%20I've%20had%20to%20navigate%20these%20differences%20and%20assimilate%20into%20the%20work%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2215e5e534-6c4c-4cbe-ab83-1a20b716258f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20I%20got%20a%20job%20at%20a%20New%20York%20tech%20startup%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20studied%20business%20law%20at%20college%20in%20Ukraine%20but%20decided%20I%20wanted%20to%20follow%20my%20passion%20and%20become%20a%20designer.%20I%20started%20studying%20graphic%20design%20online%20and%20taught%20myself%20how%20to%20use%20design%20tools.%20I%20landed%20my%20first%20job%20as%20a%20web%20designer%20in%202012%2C%20working%20for%20a%20sporting%20goods%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20at%20three%20other%20companies%20in%20Ukraine%20before%20moving%20to%20the%20US%2C%20doing%20UX%20and%20product%20design.%20I%20felt%20that%20every%20role%20I%20had%20added%20to%20my%20arsenal%20of%20skills.%20My%20last%20role%20before%20moving%20was%20as%20a%20product%20designer%20for%20SoftServe%2C%20a%20tech%20giant%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20UpTop%20gave%20me%20an%20offer%2C%20we%20discussed%20visa%20options%20for%20my%20move%20to%20the%20US.%20Because%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20formal%20education%20in%20the%20tech%20field%2C%20I%20wasn't%20eligible%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-startups-sponsor-h1b-work-visas-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EH1-B%20visa%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20company%20decided%20to%20apply%20for%20an%20O-1%20visa%20for%20%26quot%3Bextraordinary%26quot%3B%20professionals%20on%20my%20behalf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20hired%20an%20immigration%20attorney%20who%20talked%20me%20through%20the%20documents%20I'd%20need%20for%20the%20process.%20I%20gathered%20proof%20of%20my%20professional%20competency%2C%20including%20awards%2C%20media%20interviews%2C%20and%20letters%20from%20previous%20managers.%20I%20launched%20my%20own%20design%20project%2C%20Interaction%20Library%2C%20in%202016%2C%20which%20had%20already%20gotten%20attention%20online.%20I%20think%20this%20also%20helped%20me%20secure%20the%20visa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20at%20UpTop%20for%20around%20a%20year%20and%20then%20moved%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fromance-scammer-peter-gray-tinder-fraud-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETinder%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202018%20as%20a%20lead%20product%20designer.%20I%20left%20in%20September%202019%20and%20started%20focusing%20on%20my%20own%20design%20agency%2C%20Zubko%20Studio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22df767ff9-129b-47b3-b8d3-56b9e46252ec%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20are%20more%20attached%20to%20their%20work%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20a%20great%20place%20to%20work%20with%20many%20opportunities.%20I%20love%20that%20it's%20progressive%20and%20more%20culturally%20diverse%20than%20Ukraine.%20When%20I%20arrived%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20immerse%20myself%20in%20the%20community%20and%20get%20a%20feel%20for%20living%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20tech%20sector%20is%20more%20consultancy-based.%20Money%20comes%20from%20overseas%2C%20from%20companies%20who%20outsource%20their%20IT%20needs%20to%20us.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20I%20feel%20that%20big%20companies%20are%20developing%20original%20ideas%20and%20patents%2C%20while%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20provide%20consultancy%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20feel%20that%20people%20are%20much%20more%20attached%20to%20their%20work%20in%20the%20US%20because%20they%20are%20working%20on%20their%20ideas.%20In%20Ukraine%2C%20I%20worked%20with%20overseas%20clients%2C%20executing%20tasks%20for%20other%20companies%20and%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20SoftServe%2C%20I%20was%20placed%20on%20a%20project%20for%20Deloitte.%20They%20had%20established%20brand%20guidelines%2C%20which%20presented%20limitations%20for%20me%20as%20a%20designer.%20I%20couldn't%20create%20many%20new%20user%20interface%20elements%20from%20scratch%20and%20had%20to%20use%20the%20ones%20from%20the%20guide.%20I%20felt%20less%20ownership%20over%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20I've%20worked%20on%20projects%20and%20products%20I've%20felt%20more%20ownership%20of%20in%20the%20US.%20As%20a%20product%20design%20director%20at%20UpTop%2C%20I%20could%20choose%20which%20features%20to%20research%20and%20test%20and%20decide%20how%20a%20certain%20feature%20would%20be%20implemented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20the%20responsibility%2C%20but%20it's%20been%20much%20more%20challenging%20not%20to%20take%20my%20work%20home.%20There%20were%20nights%20when%20I%20couldn't%20fall%20asleep%20because%20I%20was%20thinking%20about%20ideas%20for%20the%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e23a58e9-ce1a-4b4d-bc22-bf26b5d673bc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20ideas%20and%20pitching%20are%20prioritized%20over%20execution%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Ukraine%2C%20my%20work%20was%20about%20execution.%20Because%20my%20work%20was%20in%20consulting%2C%20ideas%20came%20from%20our%20clients%2C%20and%20I%20focused%20on%20implementing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20ideation%20is%20more%20important%20than%20execution%20in%20the%20startup%20world%2C%20particularly%20because%20the%20tech%20scene%20is%20more%20saturated.%20Big%20ideas%20sell.%20They're%20how%20you%20sell%20to%20investors%20and%20raise%20funds.%20I%20think%20this%20is%20a%20positive%20difference%20%E2%80%94%20a%20great%20product%20should%20start%20with%20an%20idea%2C%20which%20you%20test%20over%20and%20over%20to%20make%20sure%20it's%20worth%20investing%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Tinder%2C%20most%20of%20my%20time%20was%20spent%20on%20idea%20generation%20and%20testing.%20I%20animated%20and%20presented%20over%2020%20versions%20of%20Tinder's%20app%2C%20and%20used%20A%2FB%20testing%20methods%20to%20understand%20what%20ideas%20were%20worth%20implementing.%20I%20worked%20on%20several%20products%20that%20made%20the%20user%20experience%20more%20seamless%2C%20including%20Tinder%20U%2C%20Tinder%20Gold%20Home%2C%20and%20Super%20Boost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployers-want-soft-skills-good-communication-teamwork-leadership-energetic-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeople%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20highly%20valued%20in%20US%20companies.%20Having%20spoken%20in%20Russian%20and%20