t-may-not-guarantee-home-in-brand-new-project-in-prime-locality%2Farticleshow%2F110146119.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20Delhi-NCR%20real%20estate%20market%2C%20challenges%20for%20middle-class%20buyers%20persist%20as%20developers%20focus%20on%20high-value%20projects.%20With%20homes%20priced%20at%20Rs%206%20crore%20and%20above%20selling%20out%20within%20hours%20of%20launch%2C%20developers%20are%20not%20inclined%20to%20launch%20smaller%20sized%20apartments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20BUSINESS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Can't%20End%2027-Week%20Pregnancy%2C%20Foetus%20Has%20Fundamental%20Right%20To%20Live%3A%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20refused%20to%20entertain%20a%20plea%20of%20a%2020-year-old%20unmarried%20woman%20seeking%20termination%20of%20her%20over%2027-week%20pregnancy%2C%20saying%20the%20foetus%20in%20the%20womb%20also%20has%20a%20fundamental%20right%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20headed%20by%20Justice%20B%20R%20Gavai%20passed%20the%20order%20while%20hearing%20the%20woman's%20plea%20challenging%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court's%20May%203%20order%20refusing%20to%20allow%20termination%20of%20her%20pregnancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20pass%20any%20order%20contrary%20to%20the%20statute%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%2C%20also%20comprising%20justices%20S%20V%20N%20Bhatti%20and%20Sandeep%20Mehta%2C%20told%20her%20counsel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20child%20in%20womb%20also%20has%20a%20fundamental%20right%20to%20live.%20What%20do%20you%20say%20about%20that%3F%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20woman's%20counsel%20said%20the%20Medical%20Termination%20of%20Pregnancy%20(MTP)%20Act%20talks%20about%20the%20mother%20only.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20made%20for%20mother%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20the%20duration%20of%20pregnancy%20was%20over%20seven%20months%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20about%20the%20right%20of%20the%20child%20to%20survive%3F%20How%20do%20you%20address%20that%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20counsel%20said%20the%20foetus%20is%20in%20the%20womb%20and%20till%20the%20child%20is%20delivered%2C%20it%20is%20the%20right%20of%20the%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20petitioner%20at%20this%20stage%20is%20under%20severe%20traumatic%20condition.%20She%20can't%20come%20outside%20also.%20She%20is%20taking%20classes%20for%20NEET%20exam.%20She%20is%20under%20highly%20traumatic%20condition.%20She%20can't%20face%20the%20society%20at%20this%20stage%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyer%20argued%20that%20her%20mental%20and%20physical%20well-being%20should%20be%20considered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSorry%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20May%203%20order%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20noted%20that%20on%20April%2025%2C%20the%20court%20had%20directed%20the%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%20(AIIMS)%20to%20constitute%20a%20medical%20board%20to%20ascertain%20the%20condition%20of%20the%20foetus%20and%20the%20petitioner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20perusal%20of%20the%20report%20(of%20medical%20board)%20shows%20that%20there%20is%20no%20congenital%20abnormality%20in%20the%20foetus%20nor%20is%20there%20any%20danger%20to%20the%20mother%20to%20carry%20on%20with%20the%20pregnancy%20which%20will%20mandate%20termination%20of%20the%20foetus%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20high%20court%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20the%20foetus%20is%20viable%20and%20normal%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20danger%20to%20the%20petitioner%20to%20carry%20on%20with%20the%20pregnancy%2C%20foeticide%20would%20neither%20be%20ethical%20nor%20legally%20permissible%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20high%20court%2C%20the%20petitioner%20had%20said%20that%20on%20April%2016%2C%20she%20felt%20discomfort%20in%20the%20abdomen%20and%20got%20an%20ultrasound%20scan%20done%20and%20it%20showed%20she%20was%2027%20weeks%20pregnant%2C%20which%20was%20beyond%20the%20legally%20permissible%20limit%20of%2024%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20MTP%20Act%2C%20termination%20of%20pregnancy%20of%20a%20duration%20exceeding%2024%20weeks%20can%20be%20allowed%20in%20case%20of%20substantial%20foetal%20abnormality%20as%20diagnosed%20by%20a%20medical%20board%20or%20if%20an%20opinion%20is%20formed%20in%20good%20faith%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20saving%20the%20life%20of%20the%20pregnant%20woman.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715767380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-02%2Fa1ooga8_supreme-court-of-india_650x400_14_February_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcant-terminate-27-week-pregnancy-foetus-has-fundamental-right-to-live-supreme-court-5668398%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20refused%20to%20entertain%20a%20plea%20of%20a%2020-year-old%20unmarried%20woman%20seeking%20termination%20of%20her%20over%2027-week%20pregnancy%2C%20saying%20the%20foetus%20in%20the%20womb%20also%20has%20a%20fundamental%20right%20to%20live.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcant-terminate-27-week-pregnancy-foetus-has-fundamental-right-to-live-supreme-court-5668398%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcant-terminate-27-week-pregnancy-foetus-has-fundamental-right-to-live-supreme-court-5668398%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcant-terminate-27-week-pregnancy-foetus-